metadata.name: Liquid mushroom
metadata.description: In the classical water drop formation technique, a drop is dropping into a water container which creates a water jet as a result of surface tension. If you drop another one into this rising jet and let them collide, liquid droplets will form. Photos, which were created with this technique, are called " drop photos." A lot of effort has been put into the creation of the photographs in this collection.  This photo is 1498 x 2000 pixels.
